					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466570#post-1980226</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466570/scp-1600#post-1980226</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 28 Feb 2014 06:41:23 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>anqxyr</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>966960</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Mercury was at room temperature during that test, and is mostly a fluke. The Foundation doesn't really understand why some substances are transformed and some aren't, so &quot;only affects solids&quot; is a close enough approximation. None of the other liquids that the Foundation tested where affected at the very least. Whether it's because mercury is so dense, or because it's a component of 1600-1, they once again don't know.</p> <p>The composition of 1600-1 comes from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_element#Medieval_alchemy">Jabir's elemental system</a>.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
