					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466570#post-1452046</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466570/scp-1600#post-1452046</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 18 May 2012 00:03:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DocPyro</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>444179</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm a little disturbed that it was cross-tested even once. It's kind of contrary to the entire purpose of SCP to say &quot;Hey, let's throw incredibly dangerous thing 1 at incredibly dangerous thing 2 and see what happens!&quot;</p> <p>&#8230; okay, I can imagine certain researchers doing just that. There are a few that seem to think the only proper punctuation for the end of a paragraph is &quot;It'll be a hoot!&quot;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
